# Frontend architecture

## Stack

Lit 3 + TypeScript + Vite. **No React, Vue, Tailwind, or external UI libraries.**

## Components

- Tag: `solar-<kebab-name>`; file `kebab-name.ts`; class `PascalCase`
- Default **shadow DOM**; light DOM only when global tokens must hit native inputs (login page: `createRenderRoot() { return this; }`)
- User-facing components: `LocaleController` in constructor + `t("dotted.key")` for all strings
- Panels/views/cards/inputs live in `frontend/src/components/`; shared logic in top-level `src/` (`api.ts`, `toast.ts`, `charts.ts`, …)

```typescript
@customElement("solar-example-panel")
export class ExamplePanel extends LitElement {
  constructor() {
    super();
    new LocaleController(this);
  }
  static styles = [sharedStyles, css`/* component-only */`];
}
```

## State (no Redux/Zustand)

- App-level `@state()` on `SolarApp` (`app-root.ts`): session, status, tab, config, entities
- Live telemetry: `LiveSocket` WebSocket (`api.ts`); 60s polling for forecast/plan/config
- Child coordination: **`window` custom events** prefixed `solar-*`:
  `solar-plan-refresh`, `solar-forecast-refresh`, `solar-navigate-tab`, `solar-history-nav-change`,
  `solar-load-shedding-dirty`, `solar-theme-change`, `solar-locale-change`, `solar-date-format-change`,
  `solar-toast-show|update|dismiss`
- `localStorage`: `solar-theme`, `solar-tab`, `solar-locale`, `solar-date-format`, `solar-api-token`

## Routing

No router library. Tab state + `localStorage` (`solar-tab`) + URL hash (`#overview`, `#history/timeline`, …).

## Async UX

Use `runWithToast()` (`toast.ts`) for operator actions; dispatch `solar-plan-refresh` after mutations.

## Anti-patterns

Do not introduce a state library, CSS framework, or SPA router without an explicit project decision.

## Keep this rule current

Update when you change custom event names, `localStorage` keys, component layout, or app shell structure. Full UX spec: [`docs/frontend-manual.md`](docs/frontend-manual.md).
